Associate Director For Safety, Operations, And Traffic Engineering

Notes:
Vdot Is Involved In The Pfs Led By Fhwa As You Stated. We Are Most Interested In The Change Interval (Yellow Time) Research As We Believe It Is Overestimated For Left-Turn Lanes Using The New Extended Kinematic Equation. Specifically, We Are Interested In Research On The Entering Speeds For Left-Turning Vehicles, The Deceleration Rate(S) For Vehicles Approaching In The Left-Turn Lane When The Light Is Still Green, And The Perception-Reaction Time For Motorists Approaching In The Left-Turn Lanes. We Think The Default Values Used In The Extended Kinematic Equation For These Areas May Not Be Accurate And May Result In Unnecessarily Long Yellow Change Intervals.
We Are Not As Concerned With The Clearance Interval (All-Red) Calculation At This Time.
